honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class NetworkGeneralSettings_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.NetworkGeneralSettings_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NetworkGeneralSettings_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Network General Settings data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1Primary Interface
    2Network Password for WEB and TELNET
    3SNMP Enable
    4Telnet Enable
    5FTP Enable
    6HTTP Enable
    7LPD Enable
    8NetBIOS Enable
    9Netcenter Enable
    10Gratuitous ARP Period
    24WIFI Type
    25Connected State
    26IP Acquired
    27Network Ready
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • NetworkGeneralSettings_DPL

        public NetworkGeneralSettings_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
